Drizzle @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a hot #medium pan{}. Add @fully cooked beef meatballs{8%ounce} and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned all over, ~{3-5%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{}.

> TIP: While meatballs brown, move on to the next step!

Wash and dry produce.

Finely dice half the @onion{1}(diced) (all for 4). Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}(thinly sliced) and thinly slice leaves.

Mix @Italian dressing{1.5%ounce} and @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} in a #small bowl{}.

> TIP: If the meatballs are still browning, assemble and plate the salad now!

Lower heat under pan used for meatballs and drizzle with oil. Add diced onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Whisk in @water{1/4%cup}, @tomato paste{1}, @marinara sauce{1}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, and @sugar{1/4%teaspoon}.

> 1/2 cup water and 1/2 tsp sugar for 4 servings.

Add meatballs back to pan with sauce; stir to coat. Remove from heat and sprinkle with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}. Cover with #lid{} and set aside to let cheese melt.

> TIP: While cheese melts, toast your bread!

Halve and toast @demi-baguette{2}.

In a #large bowl{}, toss lettuce, @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}, and @croutons{1}(crushed in the bag with your hands first) with as much dressing as you like.

Top bottom baguette halves with cheesy meatballs and sauce. Close subs and serve with salad.